<TITLE> Dhaka stocks open steady </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 30 (bdnews24.com) Dhaka stocks opened steady on the first day of the week. The Dhaka Stock Exchange Sunday saw a steep rise in the general index after the first hour of trade but started declining on the second hour and continued to do so through the midday session. At 11.39 am, the DGEN or general index was down 2.42 points or 0.08 percent at 3001.45. The DSI or all share price index rose 0.61 points or 0.02 percent to 2523.84. Turnover on the country's prime bourse was at Tk 475.505 million from trading of 1,724,749 shares. Of the traded issues, 84 gained, 73 lost and 10 issues remained unchanged. At 11.47 am, market major Square Pharma appeared at the peak of the top share board by value. It was selling high at Tk 3592 from Thursday's closing price of Tk 3546.50. UCBL rose to Tk 4190 from Thursday's Tk 3989 on reports it would announce schedules for the pending AGMs. Power Grid Company of Bangladesh was selling at Tk 692.50, up from the previous day's closing of Tk 675. Trading of the company's shares will remain suspended on Jan 1, according to a notice posted on the DSE website. City Bank declined to Tk 716.5 from Tk 717.25. NBL edged up to Tk 1460 from Thursday's 1459.5. Among the other issues on the top share board by valueIslami Bank, Fareast Life Insurance, National Life Insurance and Southeast Bankdeclined. Prim Bank gained. bdn
